19/12/2002
ANKARA, Turkey -- On Wednesday (18 December), authorities approved TV and radio broadcasts in Kurdish and other minority languages, in accordance with a new law.
It requires Turkish state TV to broadcast limited news and cultural programmes in the languages of the country's larger minority groups.
Television programmes are limited to 30 minutes a day or two hours a week.
Radio programmes would be limited to 45 minutes a day, or four hours a week.
However, representatives of state TV said they were not prepared to start broadcasting in minority languages.
(Turkish Daily News - 18/12/02)
